{"mode":"repetition","description":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Analyze the images and questions carefully to guess the correct answers.<\/strong><\/p>\n","dialogs":[{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What do you mean by local technology?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The technologies which are simple in structure, reliable in nature, cheap and easy to use in our daily life is called local technology.<\/strong><\/p>\n","image":{"path":"images\/image-60e5d8cfa410f.jpg","mime":"image\/jpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":672,"height":417}},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Water mill is a water wheel or water turbine to drive a mechanical process used in the production of many material goods.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Is it true or false?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>True<\/strong><\/p>\n","image":{"path":"images\/image-611cd66d01636.jpg","mime":"image\/jpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":640,"height":427}},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>A compass is a device that shows directions used for navigation and geographic orientation<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Is it true or false?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>True<\/strong><\/p>\n","image":{"path":"images\/image-60e5d99064e02.jpg","mime":"image\/jpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":474,"height":316}},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What is doko used for?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Doko is used to carry things like vegetables, gagri, herbs, etc.<\/strong><\/p>\n","image":{"path":"images\/image-60e5e143b42b5.jpg","mime":"image\/jpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":683,"height":1024}},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What is Aaran?<\/stron